(711, 'upper class brother brother relationship scotland poetry based on novel mentor becoming an adult professor literature intellectually gifted plagiarism literature competition private school manuscript seclusion pulitzer prize dying and death idol friendship unsociability high school scholarship father figure', 'Finding Forrester', 'Gus van Sant tells the story of a young African American man named Jamal who confronts his talents while living on the streets of the Bronx. He accidentally runs into an old writer named Forrester who discovers his passion for writing. With help from his new mentor Jamal receives a scholarship to a private school.', 'en', 19.043286, 7, 'Drama', 'Gus Van Sant', 'Sean Connery Rob Brown F. Murray Abraham'),
(712, 'upper class love at first sight wedding vows marriage proposal yuppie love of one\'s life lone wolf snob witness bride bridegroom bridesmaid funeral clumsy fellow friendship wedding gay couple', 'Four Weddings and a Funeral', 'Four Weddings And A Funeral is a British comedy about a British Man named Charles and an American Woman named Carrie who go through numerous weddings before they determine if they are right for one another.', 'en', 29.834065, 6.6, 'Comedy Drama Romance', '', 'Hugh Grant Andie MacDowell James Fleet'),
(713, 'love triangle scotland mother adultery sexuality jealousy culture clash isolation eroticism strangeness penalty violent husband new zealand maori arranged marriage piano lessons settler wilderness deceived husband marriage secret love woman director', 'The Piano', 'After a long voyage from Scotland, pianist Ada McGrath and her young daughter, Flora, are left with all their belongings, including a piano, on a New Zealand beach. Ada, who has been mute since childhood, has been sold into marriage to a local man named Alisdair Stewart. Making little attempt to warm up to Alisdair, Ada soon becomes intrigued by his Maori-friendly acquaintance, George Baines, leading to tense, life-altering conflicts.', 'en', 17.681707, 7.1, 'Drama Romance', 'Jane Campion', 'Holly Hunter Harvey Keitel Sam Neill'),
(714, 'london england england spy china news broadcast intelligence television missile manipulation of the media secret intelligence service special car tv station media tycoon navy motorcycle secret service hamburg germany', 'Tomorrow Never Dies', 'A deranged media mogul is staging international incidents to pit the world\'s superpowers against each other. Now 007 must take on this evil mastermind in an adrenaline-charged battle to end his reign of terror and prevent global pandemonium.', 'en', 42.887121, 6, 'Adventure Action Thriller', 'Roger Spottiswoode', 'Pierce Brosnan Jonathan Pryce Michelle Yeoh'),
