(14292, 'olympic games sport ice hockey milwaukee wisconsin st. paul minnesota gas rationing lake placid new york aftercreditsstinger duringcreditsstinger', 'Miracle', 'In 1980, the United States Ice Hockey team\'s coach, Herb Brooks, put a ragtag squad of college kids up against the legendary juggernaut from the Soviet Union at the Olympic Games. Despite the long odds, Team USA carried the pride of a nation yearning for a distraction from world events. With the world watching, the team rose to the occasion, prompting broadcaster Al Michaels\' now famous question to the millions viewing at home: \"Do you believe in miracles?\" Yes!', 'en', 7.534003, 7, 'Drama History', 'Gavin O\'Connor', 'Kurt Russell Patricia Clarkson Noah Emmerich'),
